  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>You prepare a special pattern to your Chakra, allowing you to activate (and deactivate) a 'non-detection field' on your turn, as a free action. Each round this field is active costs 1 Chakra. While the field is active, any creature that would detect the user by scent, sound or sight must make a save to avoid dismissing you as an unimportant detail, allowing you to hide while being observed, even without any cover. If you remain stationary, you also gain a +2 bonus to your Hide checks against creatures who failed their save. Each time you are outside of a creature's line of sight for at least 5 rounds, it must make a new save to resist the technique (even if it had failed before).<br><br>Certain conditions may make the field ineffective, such as standing alone in a nearly featureless room, not having enough details to 'blend in' with.<br><br>This technique cannot be dispelled.</p>\n\n\n\n",
      "summary": "",
